(Apache Kafka is an open-source message broker project developed by the Apache Software Foundation written in Scala. ,1)
(Apache Kafka is publish-subscribe based fault tolerant messaging system. ,3)
(Apache Kafka was originated at LinkedIn and later became an open sourced Apache project in 2011, then First-class Apache project in 2012.,2)
(Each broker can handle terabytes of messages without performance impact.,1)
(It is fast, scalable and distributed by design.,3)
(It is, in its essence, a "massively scalable pub/sub message queue architected as a distributed transaction log,"making it highly valuable for enterprise infrastructures to process streaming data.,1)
(Kafka is written in Scala and Java. ,3)
(Messages are persisted on disk and replicated within the cluster to prevent data loss. ,1)
(The design is heavily influenced by transaction logs,1)
(The project aims to provide a unified, high-throughput, low-latency platform for handling real-time data feeds. ,1)
